stylometry:
If you price a product/service too high, demand will drop because people will not have enough money to afford it. However, if you price the product/service too low, the demand may skyrocket beyond your means of manufacturing and your profits may not even cover the cost of production.

So as a manager, you must find the happy medium between the price and demand that allows you to manufacture within your business' means, while also keeping the price high enough to control demand and make a profit. You can easily find this by creating a graph of the price and demand, and by landing on a value right in the middle for setting the price.
